{"id": "demo-d-001-notecraft-2026-05-20", "record": {"agent_version": "vrt-agent-v0.10.0-function-function:_call:-prompt-69ef583c6dbe", "classification_rationale": "Vendor's AI is used exclusively for productivity assistance (sentence completion in internal notes) with no decisioning role and no customer-facing exposure. Disclosed features are human-initiated and human-confirmed throughout. Vendor states no PII processing in AI context and no customer-content retention beyond a 24-hour sync cache. SOC 2 Type II attestation current. The use case sits at the productivity-only floor of the risk taxonomy and does not implicate the regulated-decision provisions of OSFI E-23 or NIST AI RMF's high-risk categories.", "confidence_signal": {"interpretation": "high", "score": 0.92}, "correlation_id": "8d90a4a76a1249f8", "decision_id": "d-9ecab1e7-1a07-4988-a157-3d72b6021585", "decision_timestamp": "2026-05-28T14:56:07.682261Z", "evidence_cited": [{"input_field_reference": "$.ai_usage_level", "reasoning": "Reported as 'productivity_only', the lowest tier in the AI usage taxonomy. Places the vendor at the Tier 1 floor per docs/phase-0/01-risk-classification.md."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.ai_features_disclosed[0].autonomy", "reasoning": "Meeting note autocomplete is 'human_initiated' (the user types and the model suggests completions in response). No autonomous action; no decisioning."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.ai_features_disclosed[1].decision_role", "reasoning": "Smart formatting is 'none' for decision role: it applies markdown to plain text, no semantic decision."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.pii_processing_claims.processes_pii", "reasoning": "Vendor explicitly states no PII processing. Combined with the productivity-only scope, this removes the primary risk drivers (data residency exposure, model training on customer content) that would elevate the tier."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.compliance_attestations[0]", "reasoning": "Current SOC 2 Type II attestation (dated 2025-08-15, 12 month validity) satisfies the baseline security control attestation expected for Tier 1 SaaS vendors."}], "input_schema_version": "1.0.0", "input_submission_id": "demo-vendor-001-notecraft", "output_schema_version": "1.3.0", "recommended_disposition": "approve", "regulatory_framework_tags": ["OSFI_E_23"], "review_interval_days": 365, "risk_tier": "tier_1_low", "tenant_id": "__default__"}}
{"id": "demo-d-002-converseai-2026-05-21", "record": {"agent_version": "vrt-agent-v0.10.0-function-function:_call:-prompt-69ef583c6dbe", "classification_rationale": "Vendor operates a customer-facing AI ticket-triage system that processes customer-supplied message content (including incidental PII) but routes only to human agents who handle all customer-facing communication. The AI does not respond to customers directly and operates under human-confirmed autonomy. Combined with current SOC 2 Type II and ISO 27001 attestations, a signed DPA, and disclosed sub-processor inventory, the use case fits Tier 2 moderate. Conditional approval is warranted because the model receives PII in real time and the 90-day transcript retention requires periodic verification of stated controls.", "confidence_signal": {"interpretation": "moderate", "score": 0.78}, "correlation_id": "e5dbaf66969a489a", "decision_id": "d-e998517b-23af-4fb5-b6d5-e8fdeeef8f3c", "decision_timestamp": "2026-05-28T14:56:07.719378Z", "evidence_cited": [{"input_field_reference": "$.ai_usage_level", "reasoning": "Reported as 'customer_facing', which under the risk taxonomy places the vendor in the Tier 2-3 band. The 'human_confirmed' autonomy on all features pulls the classification toward Tier 2 rather than Tier 3."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.ai_features_disclosed[0].autonomy", "reasoning": "Ticket triage is 'human_confirmed': the AI routes to a human agent queue, but the human agent makes the customer-facing decision. The human-in-the-loop precondition holds."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.ai_features_disclosed[2].description", "reasoning": "Suggested reply drafts are reviewed and edited by human agents before sending. The model does not autonomously communicate with customers."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.pii_processing_claims.categories", "reasoning": "Customer name, contact information, and incidental PII in message content are processed in real time. Vendor states no model fine-tuning on customer content. The PII flow elevates the tier from Tier 1 productivity to Tier 2 moderate."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.pii_processing_claims.handling_notes", "reasoning": "Vendor states 90-day transcript retention and PII masking on account numbers. The 90-day window introduces a re-review trigger; transcript handling controls warrant verification."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.vendor_disclosed_subprocessors[0]", "reasoning": "Anthropic disclosed as sub-processor for model inference, with stated no-training-use commitment in DPA. The disclosure satisfies the model-supply-chain transparency expectation for Tier 2."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.compliance_attestations", "reasoning": "SOC 2 Type II (2025-11) and ISO 27001 (2025-06) both current. Both attestations are expected at this tier; absence of either would force escalation."}], "input_schema_version": "1.0.0", "input_submission_id": "demo-vendor-002-converseai", "output_schema_version": "1.3.0", "recommended_disposition": "conditional_approve", "regulatory_framework_tags": ["OSFI_E_23"], "required_mitigations": ["Verify the no-training-use commitment against the actual Anthropic DPA at contract renewal.", "Quarterly review of transcript-retention controls (90-day purge) and PII-masking efficacy on account numbers.", "Monitor for scope expansion from human-confirmed reply drafts toward customer-facing autonomous response, which would re-trigger Tier 3 review.", "Confirm Canadian-region data pinning is actually applied for in-scope tenants (vendor states the option exists; deploying-organization configuration must enable it)."], "review_interval_days": 180, "risk_tier": "tier_2_moderate", "tenant_id": "__default__"}}
{"id": "demo-d-003-textlens-2026-05-22", "record": {"accountable_owner": "Chief Risk Officer or designated Senior Vendor Risk Manager", "agent_version": "vrt-agent-v0.10.0-function-function:_call:-prompt-69ef583c6dbe", "classification_rationale": "Vendor uses AI for operational decisioning on KYC and loan-document intake, processing high-sensitivity PII (SIN, government IDs, financial records) through both proprietary vision models and a third-party fallback (OpenAI). Cross-border data flow (CA customer data routed to US OpenAI on low-confidence pages) plus the absence of a current ISO 27001 attestation together raise the tier from operational Tier 2 to elevated Tier 3. Senior review is recommended over conditional approval because the OpenAI fallback path is the most material risk and warrants explicit decisioning by an accountable owner rather than a delegated approval.", "confidence_signal": {"interpretation": "moderate", "score": 0.74}, "correlation_id": "520a6986a977468e", "decision_id": "d-5efef501-9d9a-4afd-a19e-a3815aaaf7c3", "decision_timestamp": "2026-05-28T14:56:07.726787Z", "evidence_cited": [{"input_field_reference": "$.ai_usage_level", "reasoning": "Reported as 'operational_decisions'. Combined with the high-sensitivity PII categories disclosed below, this sits at the Tier 3 boundary rather than Tier 2."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.pii_processing_claims.categories", "reasoning": "Categories include SIN and government ID numbers (high-sensitivity per docs/phase-1 PII taxonomy). For a Canadian deploying organization, SIN handling brings PIPEDA and OSFI E-23 sensitivity expectations into scope."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.ai_features_disclosed[0].description", "reasoning": "Identity document OCR feeds the KYC flow. KYC is a regulated decision under both AML guidance and OSFI E-23 onboarding controls; the AI is in the operational pre-decision step but materially shapes the human decision."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.model_providers", "reasoning": "OpenAI listed as fallback for low-confidence pages. This is a cross-border AI sub-processor receiving PII (redacted on first-pass detection, but vision OCR cannot guarantee complete pre-redaction). The fallback path is the most material risk in the submission."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.data_residency.conditions", "reasoning": "Canadian customer data pinned to ca-central-1 in vendor's primary path, but OpenAI fallback calls go to US. The conditional-residency arrangement requires explicit consent capture and audit trail."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.compliance_attestations", "reasoning": "SOC 2 Type II is current (2025-09) but no ISO 27001 listed. For a vendor in the KYC pre-decisioning path, ISO 27001 is the expected control attestation; absence is a gap, not a blocker."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.vendor_disclosed_subprocessors[1]", "reasoning": "OpenAI Inc. disclosed as US-based subprocessor processing customer data. Disclosure is correct; the underlying flow is the elevated-risk path."}], "input_schema_version": "1.0.0", "input_submission_id": "demo-vendor-003-textlens", "output_schema_version": "1.3.0", "recommended_disposition": "escalate_senior_review", "regulatory_framework_tags": ["OSFI_E_23", "NIST_AI_RMF"], "required_mitigations": ["Obtain explicit DPA addendum from TextLens covering OpenAI fallback path: data minimization, no-retention guarantee, and PII-redaction verification before contract execution.", "Require ISO 27001 certification (or equivalent control attestation) within 12 months as a condition of continued use.", "Configure enterprise-tier ca-central-1 pinning for primary OCR path; obtain written confirmation that the configuration is applied.", "Implement runtime monitoring on the OpenAI fallback trigger rate; investigate if fallback exceeds 5% of documents (indicates pre-redaction is ineffective).", "Quarterly review of customer-consented production samples used for model improvement (the opt-in mechanism) to confirm opt-out rate and audit consent records."], "review_interval_days": 90, "risk_tier": "tier_3_elevated", "tenant_id": "__default__"}}
{"id": "demo-d-004-autocredit-2026-05-23", "record": {"agent_version": "vrt-agent-v0.10.0-function-function:_call:-prompt-69ef583c6dbe", "classification_rationale": "Vendor offers a fully autonomous credit decisioning system intended for direct deployment on personal loan applications, with the vendor recommending autonomous deployment up to $25,000. The use case is a regulated decision in every relevant framework: it materially affects consumers, triggers ECOA adverse-action notice requirements, falls under EU AI Act Annex III (creditworthiness assessment is explicitly enumerated as high-risk), and would trigger OSFI E-23 model-risk-management requirements for any Canadian deployment. Two material defects support rejection rather than escalation: (1) the vendor's only model-fairness audit is from 2024, predating the 2025 model version 7 release referenced in the model card, and is available only under NDA, which prevents the deploying organization from satisfying its own independent-validation obligation under OSFI E-23; (2) the vendor states the model would require re-training and re-auditing for Canadian deployment but provides no commitment, scope, or timeline for that work. Rejection does not foreclose future engagement; it directs the vendor to address these gaps before re-submission.", "confidence_signal": {"interpretation": "high", "score": 0.88}, "correlation_id": "a4cf1570ee6b4a6b", "decision_id": "d-ce352967-60d7-4b24-94bd-65e19598d0e2", "decision_timestamp": "2026-05-28T14:56:07.733361Z", "evidence_cited": [{"input_field_reference": "$.ai_usage_level", "reasoning": "Reported as 'regulated_decisions', the highest tier in the AI usage taxonomy. Anchors the classification at Tier 4 absent unusual mitigation."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.ai_features_disclosed[0].autonomy", "reasoning": "Automated credit decisioning is 'autonomous'. The vendor explicitly recommends autonomous deployment for applications below $25,000. Autonomous regulated decisioning is the Tier 4 threshold."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.ai_features_disclosed[0].description", "reasoning": "Binary approve/decline decisions on $5K-$50K personal loans. Materiality to consumers is direct and significant. Falls within EU AI Act Annex III 5(b) (creditworthiness assessment) and within OSFI E-23 model-risk-management scope for any Canadian deployment."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.documentation_artifacts", "reasoning": "No independent model-fairness audit report is provided in the submission. The model card references a 2024 audit available only under NDA. For a Tier 4 regulated-decisions vendor, the deploying organization needs an independent validation it can place in its own audit file."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.pii_processing_claims.categories", "reasoning": "Vendor processes SSN, full credit reports, and consented bank transaction history. This is the most sensitive PII category in the framework. Combined with autonomous decisioning, it triggers heightened scrutiny under every applicable regulatory framework."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.data_residency.conditions", "reasoning": "Vendor states model cannot currently support Canadian deployment without re-training on Canadian credit bureau data and re-auditing. No timeline or commitment provided. This makes cross-border use of the existing model untenable for any Canadian-incorporated deploying organization."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.ai_act_self_classification", "reasoning": "Vendor self-classifies as 'high_risk' under EU AI Act. Self-classification is honest and consistent with the Annex III scope; it does not by itself mitigate the underlying risk."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.compliance_attestations", "reasoning": "SOC 2 Type II current (2025-06). For Tier 4 regulated decisioning, SOC 2 is necessary but not sufficient; expected attestations for this class also include independent model validation, fairness audit, and (for Canadian deployment) OSFI E-23 attestation pathway."}], "input_schema_version": "1.0.0", "input_submission_id": "demo-vendor-004-autocredit", "output_schema_version": "1.3.0", "recommended_disposition": "reject", "regulatory_framework_tags": ["EU_AI_Act_Annex_III", "OSFI_E_23", "NIST_AI_RMF", "SR_11_7"], "review_interval_days": 1, "risk_tier": "tier_4_high", "tenant_id": "__default__"}}
{"id": "demo-d-005-globalpayflow-2026-05-24", "record": {"accountable_owner": "Chief Privacy Officer or designated Data Protection Officer (EU/UK scope)", "agent_version": "vrt-agent-v0.10.0-function-function:_call:-prompt-69ef583c6dbe", "classification_rationale": "Vendor self-discloses only rule-based payment reconciliation and reports no AI model providers, no training data sources, and self-classifies as 'minimal_risk' under EU AI Act. However, the disclosed sub-processor list includes two AI-supplying services: Sift Science (machine-learning fraud scoring) and Hugging Face (hosted inference endpoint for a transaction-description classifier). Both process customer data per the disclosure. This is a self-classification inconsistency: the vendor's AI use is real and material but is concealed within the sub-processor relationship rather than disclosed as a vendor feature. Escalation is required to resolve the disclosure gap before any classification decision can be relied upon. The recommendation is not a finding against the vendor; it is a finding that the submission as constructed is insufficient for a decision.", "confidence_signal": {"interpretation": "moderate", "score": 0.71}, "correlation_id": "caa85c59ca0541ff", "decision_id": "d-cabec2aa-cf1a-45fc-9128-3d3f3d5a58b1", "decision_timestamp": "2026-05-28T14:56:07.740125Z", "evidence_cited": [{"input_field_reference": "$.ai_features_disclosed", "reasoning": "Single feature disclosed (payment reconciliation, characterized as rule-based automation rather than AI). The disclosure list does not include the AI capabilities supplied by Sift Science or Hugging Face, both of which process customer data per the sub-processor section."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.model_providers", "reasoning": "Empty. Inconsistent with the Hugging Face sub-processor relationship, which is by definition a hosted model inference endpoint. The empty field reflects how the vendor frames the relationship, not the actual technical reality."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.training_data_sources", "reasoning": "Empty. Consistent with the vendor not training its own models, but does not address the upstream training data of the Sift Science or Hugging Face models the vendor relies on."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.ai_act_self_classification", "reasoning": "Vendor self-classifies as 'minimal_risk'. Self-classification is inconsistent with the actual AI footprint surfaced by the sub-processor disclosure. Fraud scoring against customer data is at minimum a 'limited_risk' use case under EU AI Act transparency obligations and may rise to 'high_risk' depending on the autonomy of fraud decisions."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.vendor_disclosed_subprocessors[2]", "reasoning": "Sift Science disclosed as US-based subprocessor providing 'fraud scoring and risk decisioning via machine learning models', processing customer data. This is the AI use that is missing from the AI features list and that elevates the classification."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.vendor_disclosed_subprocessors[3]", "reasoning": "Hugging Face disclosed as US-based subprocessor providing 'hosted inference endpoint for transaction description classifier (sentence-transformers model)', processing customer data. Confirms a second AI processing path the vendor did not disclose at the feature level."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.pii_processing_claims.categories", "reasoning": "Beneficiary and payer names, account identifiers, transaction amounts, and reference text. The Sift Science and Hugging Face flows process this data in models, which the vendor's PII handling notes do not address."}, {"input_field_reference": "$.data_residency.regions", "reasoning": "Vendor states EU and UK residency only. Sift Science and Hugging Face sub-processors are both US-based and process customer data, creating an undisclosed cross-border transfer that conflicts with the stated residency."}], "input_schema_version": "1.0.0", "input_submission_id": "demo-vendor-005-globalpayflow", "output_schema_version": "1.3.0", "recommended_disposition": "escalate_senior_review", "regulatory_framework_tags": ["EU_AI_Act_Annex_III", "NIST_AI_RMF"], "required_mitigations": ["Vendor must amend the submission to disclose Sift Science and Hugging Face as AI features (not just sub-processors), with feature-level decision_role and autonomy fields populated.", "Vendor must re-evaluate the EU AI Act self-classification in light of fraud scoring against customer data; minimum 'limited_risk' classification expected.", "Vendor must amend data residency disclosure to reflect cross-border AI processing through US sub-processors, with SCCs or equivalent transfer mechanism documented for EU customer data.", "Re-submission with corrected disclosures triggers new triage; the resulting record supersedes this one via the supersedes field.", "Until re-submission is received, no contract execution; if existing usage exists, suspend AI-touching workflows pending clarification."], "review_interval_days": 30, "risk_tier": "tier_3_elevated", "tenant_id": "__default__"}}
